Granting the right to create databases:
as root: 
# pgsql postgres
postgres> \du   # to list users
postgres> ALTER ROLE gmaps CREATEDB;


Adding a user:
> python manage.py shell
>>> from django.contrib.auth.models import User
>>> email = 'user@domain.com'
>>> passwd = 'password'
>>> user = User.objects.create_user(email, email, passwd)
>>> user.save()


A hacky way of preserving data over a schema update (just adding a column):
>>> alter table portal_job rename to portal_jobold;
>>> \copy portal_jobold to '/tmp/old'
(python manage.py syncdb)
>>> \copy portal_job(jobid,submission_id,diskfile_id,filelicense_id,fileorigname,exposefile,calibration_id,exposejob,status,failurereason,howsolved,starttime,finishtime) from '/tmp/old'
